                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1192" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1192" type="surname" value="BUCKLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1192" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BUCKLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am butler to Mr. Snow, of Saville-row. On the 1st of April I was in the pantry, and heard somebody in the hall—I went and saw the prisoner just leaving the hall, with my coat on his back—as he was</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184304030163"></xptr>
               <p>going up the area steps he pulled the coat off, and threw it down—I pursued after him, and he was stopped at the corner of Clifford-street—this is my coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430403-name-1193" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1193" type="surname" value="M'LOCHLAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430403-name-1193" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES M'LOCHLAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I took the prisoner—this coat was given to me at the house in Saville-row.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> My grandmother sent me to Dr. Moore, who lives next door to the prosecutor, and I went down there by mistake—this coat was lying on the step, the butler came out and said, "If you don't be off, I will lock you up"—I ran off, and two men stopped me at the end of the street—I never had the coat on my back.</p>
